schema.description: A secret value used for sending hits to Measurement Protocol.

displayName.description: Required. Human-readable display name for this secret.

name.description: Output only. Resource name of this secret. This secret may be a child of any type of stream. Format: properties/{property}/dataStreams/{dataStream}/measurementProtocolSecrets/{measurementProtocolSecret}

secretValue.description: Output only. The measurement protocol secret value. Pass this value to the api_secret field of the Measurement Protocol API when sending hits to this secret's parent property.

mappings.name: Returns child MeasurementProtocolSecrets under the specified parent Property.

measurementProtocolSecrets.description: A list of secrets for the parent stream specified in the request.

mappings.name: Creates a GoogleAdsLink.

schema.description: A link between a GA4 property and a Google Ads account.

adsPersonalizationEnabled.description: Enable personalized advertising features with this integration. Automatically publish my Google Analytics audience lists and Google Analytics remarketing events/parameters to the linked Google Ads account. If this field is not set on create/update, it will be defaulted to true.

canManageClients.description: Output only. If true, this link is for a Google Ads manager account.

createTime.description: Output only. Time when this link was originally created.

creatorEmailAddress.description: Output only. Email address of the user that created the link. An empty string will be returned if the email address can't be retrieved.

name.description: Output only. Format: properties/{propertyId}/googleAdsLinks/{googleAdsLinkId} Note: googleAdsLinkId is not the Google Ads customer ID.

updateTime.description: Output only. Time when this link was last updated.

mappings.name: Lists GoogleAdsLinks on a property.

nextPageToken.description: A token, which can be sent as `page_token` to retrieve the next page. If this field is omitted, there are no subsequent pages.

mappings.name: Creates a FirebaseLink. Properties can have at most one FirebaseLink.

schema.description: A link between a GA4 property and a Firebase project.

createTime.description: Output only. Time when this FirebaseLink was originally created.

project.description: Immutable. Firebase project resource name. When creating a FirebaseLink, you may provide this resource name using either a project number or project ID. Once this resource has been created, returned FirebaseLinks will always have a project_name that contains a project number. Format: 'projects/{project number}' Example: 'projects/1234'

mappings.name: Lists FirebaseLinks on a property. Properties can have at most one FirebaseLink.

firebaseLinks.description: List of FirebaseLinks. This will have at most one value.

nextPageToken.description: A token, which can be sent as `page_token` to retrieve the next page. If this field is omitted, there are no subsequent pages. Currently, Google Analytics supports only one FirebaseLink per property, so this will never be populated.

schema.description: A definition for a custom metric.

description.description: Optional. Description for this custom dimension. Max length of 150 characters.

displayName.description: Required. Display name for this custom metric as shown in the Analytics UI. Max length of 82 characters, alphanumeric plus space and underscore starting with a letter. restrictedMetricType.description: Optional. Types of restricted data that this metric may contain. Required for metrics with CURRENCY measurement unit. Must be empty for metrics with a non-CURRENCY measurement unit.

scope.description: Required. Immutable. The scope of this custom metric.

description.description: Optional. Description for this custom dimension. Max length of 150 characters.

disallowAdsPersonalization.description: Optional. If set to true, sets this dimension as NPA and excludes it from ads personalization. This is currently only supported by user-scoped custom dimensions.

displayName.description: Required. Display name for this custom dimension as shown in the Analytics UI. Max length of 82 characters, alphanumeric plus space and underscore starting with a letter. Legacy system-generated display names may contain square brackets, but updates to this field will never permit square brackets.

name.description: Output only. Resource name for this CustomDimension resource. Format: properties/{property}/customDimensions/{customDimension}

parameterName.description: Required. Immutable. Tagging parameter name for this custom dimension. If this is a user-scoped dimension, then this is the user property name. If this is an event-scoped dimension, then this is the event parameter name. May only contain alphanumeric and underscore characters, starting with a letter. Max length of 24 characters for user-scoped dimensions, 40 characters for event-scoped dimensions.

scope.description: Required. Immutable. The scope of this dimension.

schema.description: A resource message representing a Google Analytics GA4 property.

account.description: Immutable. The resource name of the parent account Format: accounts/{account_id} Example: "accounts/123"

expireTime.description: Output only. If set, the time at which this trashed property will be permanently deleted. If not set, then this property is not currently in the trash can and is not slated to be deleted.

name.description: Output only. Resource name of this property. Format: properties/{property_id} Example: "properties/1000"

parent.description: Immutable. Resource name of this property's logical parent. Note: The Property-Moving UI can be used to change the parent. Format: accounts/{account}, properties/{property} Example: "accounts/100", "properties/101"

propertyType.description: Immutable. The property type for this Property resource. When creating a property, if the type is "PROPERTY_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED", then "ORDINARY_PROPERTY" will be implied. "SUBPROPERTY" and "ROLLUP_PROPERTY" types cannot yet be created with the Google Analytics Admin API.

serviceLevel.description: Output only. The Google Analytics service level that applies to this property.

timeZone.description: Required. Reporting Time Zone, used as the day boundary for reports, regardless of where the data originates. If the time zone honors DST, Analytics will automatically adjust for the changes. NOTE: Changing the time zone only affects data going forward, and is not applied retroactively. Format: https://www.iana.org/time-zones Example: "America/Los_Angeles"
